leadingComments.value:
*
     * Kicks of the Pratt parser, and returns the result
     * @param {number} [rbp=0] The right binding power
     * @returns {any}

*
 * A Pratt parser.
 * @example
 * const lex = perplex('1 + -2 * 3^4')
 *   .token('NUM', /\d+/)
 *   .token('+', /\+/)
 *   .token('-', /-/)
 *   .token('*', new RegExp('*'))
 *   .token('/', /\//)
 *   .token('^', /\^/)
 *   .token('(', /\(/)
 *   .token(')', /\)/)
 *   .token('$SKIP_WS', /\s+/)
 *
 * const parser = new Parser(lex)
 *   .builder()
 *   .nud('NUM', 100, t => parseInt(t.match))
 *   .nud('-', 10, (t, bp) => -parser.parse(bp))
 *   .nud('(', 10, (t, bp) => {
 *     const expr = parser.parse(bp)
 *     lex.expect(')')
 *     return expr
 *   })
 *   .bp(')', 0)
 *
 *   .led('^', 20, (left, t, bp) => Math.pow(left, parser.parse(bp - 1)))
 *   .led('+', 30, (left, t, bp) => left + parser.parse(bp))
 *   .led('-', 30, (left, t, bp) => left - parser.parse(bp))
 *   .led('*', 40, (left, t, bp) => left * parser.parse(bp))
 *   .led('/', 40, (left, t, bp) => left / parser.parse(bp))
 *   .build()
 * parser.parse()
 * // => 161

*
 * A Pratt parser.
 * @example
 * const lex = perplex('1 + -2 * 3^4')
 *   .token('NUM', /\d+/)
 *   .token('+', /\+/)
 *   .token('-', /-/)
 *   .token('*', new RegExp('*'))
 *   .token('/', /\//)
 *   .token('^', /\^/)
 *   .token('(', /\(/)
 *   .token(')', /\)/)
 *   .token('$SKIP_WS', /\s+/)
 *
 * const parser = new Parser(lex)
 *   .builder()
 *   .nud('NUM', 100, t => parseInt(t.match))
 *   .nud('-', 10, (t, bp) => -parser.parse(bp))
 *   .nud('(', 10, (t, bp) => {
 *     const expr = parser.parse(bp)
 *     lex.expect(')')
 *     return expr
 *   })
 *   .bp(')', 0)
 *
 *   .led('^', 20, (left, t, bp) => Math.pow(left, parser.parse(bp - 1)))
 *   .led('+', 30, (left, t, bp) => left + parser.parse(bp))
 *   .led('-', 30, (left, t, bp) => left - parser.parse(bp))
 *   .led('*', 40, (left, t, bp) => left * parser.parse(bp))
 *   .led('/', 40, (left, t, bp) => left / parser.parse(bp))
 *   .build()
 * parser.parse()
 * // => 161
